📱🌐 Nursy AI — Product & Build Guide (Hackathon Version)
🧠 Product Vision

Nursy AI is a mobile-first, offline-capable AI health companion that helps users:

Track daily health status
Log symptoms and medications
Detect health trends over time
Generate health insights and reports
Work offline and sync when internet is available

It is designed for real-world usability, especially in low-connectivity environments.

🧭 System Strategy (VERY IMPORTANT)
🥇 1. Mobile App (PRIMARY PRODUCT)

📱 Kotlin + Jetpack Compose app is the main user-facing product

This is what users actually use daily.

Core idea:

“Everything works offline first, then syncs to cloud intelligence.”

🥈 2. Web App (SECONDARY — REQUIRED FOR VERCEL)

🌐 Next.js app deployed on Vercel is ONLY for:

demo access
judge evaluation
data visualization
It is NOT a full product.

It is:

“A live dashboard connected to the same backend.”

📱 MOBILE APP (MAIN PRODUCT)
🔧 Tech Stack
Kotlin (Android)
Jetpack Compose (UI)
Room DB (offline storage)
WorkManager (background sync)
Retrofit (API calls)
Local rules engine (light AI logic)
🧠 Features (FULL MOBILE SYSTEM)
1. Authentication & Profile
Email login / signup
User profile
Health profile:
age
gender
weight
height
blood type
allergies
chronic conditions
2. Daily Health Check-in
Mood tracking (5 levels)
Energy level (1–10)
Sleep hours + quality
Stress level
Water intake
Notes (free text)
3. Symptom Tracking
Add symptoms (headache, fever, fatigue, etc.)
Severity (1–5)
Duration tracking
Notes per symptom
Date-based history
4. Medication Management
Add medication
Dose + frequency
Schedule reminders
Missed dose tracking
Adherence score (%)
5. Health Dashboard
Health score (0–100)
Today’s summary
Active symptoms
Medication status
Quick insights
6. Health Timeline
Chronological health history
Symptom + medication events
Daily logs visualization
7. AI Symptom Journal (Local AI)

Natural language input:

“I feel tired and have headache for 3 days”

Extracts structured data:
fatigue
headache
Auto-logs into system
8. AI Health Insights (Cloud + Local)
Local AI (on-device)
Basic rules:
symptom repetition detection
sleep vs fatigue warnings
medication reminders
Cloud AI (advanced)
Trend analysis:
symptom patterns
health deterioration detection
medication effectiveness
Weekly health report generation
9. Emergency Health Card (Offline)
Name
Blood type
Allergies
Emergency contacts
Conditions
One-tap access
10. Notifications System
Medication reminders
Check-in reminders
Appointment alerts
Hydration reminders
11. Offline Mode (VERY IMPORTANT FEATURE)
Fully functional without internet
All data stored in Room DB
Syncs automatically when online
12. Sync Engine
Local Room DB → Cloud DynamoDB
Background sync using WorkManager
Conflict-safe updates
